Containers and chests
=======================

Base object: /std/container.c
Closeable storage: /std/storage.c (inherits CONTAINER)

Transparent property
--------------------

Containers support two visibility modes when they have a lid (set_can_close(1)):

OPAQUE (default):
  set_property("transparent", 0);
  When closed: look in and inventory listing show no contents ("It is closed.").
  When open: normal contents listing and get/put work.

TRANSPARENT / GLASS:
  set_transparent(1);   /* or set_property("transparent", 1); */
  When closed: contents are visible on look in, but get/put are blocked with
  "The lid is closed."
  When open: same as opaque open (full access).

Functions
---------

  set_transparent(int n)     Set 1 for glass/see-through, 0 for opaque.
  query_transparent()        Returns current transparent flag.
  query_contents_visible()   Returns 1 if look in may show contents.
  look_in(object who)        Returns formatted contents or blocked message.

Example: glass display case
---------------------------

inherit STORAGE;

void create() {
    ::create();
    set_name("display case");
    set_short("a glass display case");
    set_can_close(1);
    set_transparent(1);
    set_closed(1);
    set_max_encumbrance(500);
}

Existing chests are unchanged: transparent defaults to 0 (opaque).
